{{Essay-like|date=December 2016}} '''FinTech''' or [[financial technology]] has emerged as a relatively new industry in [[India]].<ref>{{cite news | url=http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/jobs/fintech-sector-proving-to-be-talent-magnet/articleshow/51986723.cms | title=Fintech sector proving to be talent magnet | publisher=[[The Economic Times]] | date=26 April 2016 | accessdate=22 May 2016}}</ref> FinTech is an industry comprising companies that use technology to offer financial services. These companies operate in [[insurance]], [[asset management]] and [[payment]], and numerous other industries.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.siliconindia.com/news/business/FinTech-Gaining-Momentum-in-India-with-Paytms-Payment-Banks-nid-194947-cid-3.html | title=FinTech Gaining Momentum in India with Paytm's Payment Banks | date=2 May 2016 | accessdate=22 May 2016}}</ref>
==Market size and growth== According to the report of The National Association of Software and Services Companies ([[NASSCOM]]), India has a presence of approximately 400 companies in the fintech industry, with an investment of about $420 million (in 2015). The [[NASSCOM]] report also estimated the fintech software and services market to grow 1.7 times by 2020, making it worth $8 billion.<ref name=FE>{{cite news | url=http://www.financialexpress.com/article/industry/companies/towards-a-fintech-revolution/262870/ | title=Fintech revolution in India: Tech-finance collaboration has fired up entrepreneurs | publisher=[[The Financial Express (India)|The Financial Express]] | date=23 May 2016 | accessdate=23 May 2016}}</ref>
The Indian fintech landscape is segmented as follows – 34% in payment processing, followed by 32% in banking and 12% in the trading, public and private markets.<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.zdnet.com/article/india-emerging-as-fastest-growing-market-for-fintech-software-products/ | title=India emerging as fastest-growing market for fintech software products | publisher=[[ZDNet]] | date=3 May 2016 | accessdate=22 May 2016}}</ref> [[Seed accelerator|accelerators]] and [[business incubator|incubators]] tapping the [[startup ecosystem]] include [[PayPal]]’s Star Tank, [[Yes Bank]]’s collaboration with [[T-Hub]], among others.<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/companies/india-emerging-a-hub-for-fintech-start-ups-116051700397_1.html | title=India emerging a hub for fintech start-ups | publisher=[[Business Standard]] | date=18 May 2016 | accessdate=23 May 2016}}</ref> [[Visakhapatnam]] (Vizag) is being developed as fintech valley and the local government of Andhra Pradesh had opened [[Fintech Valley Vizag|Fintech Valley]] to promote the investments in this area.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://fintechvalleyvizag.com/|title=Fintech Valley Vizag|website=fintechvalleyvizag.com|access-date=2017-02-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.techiexpert.com/all-set-for-vizag-fintech-festival-from-today/|title=Vizag Fintech Festival|last=|first=|date=2018-10-24|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=2018-10-24|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref>
