The '''Kosovo Adyghes''' are a small group of the [[Adyghe people]] who lived in [[Kosovo]] beginning in the mid-19th century, when they [[Ethnic cleansing of Circassians|relocated]] to the [[Ottoman Empire]] after the [[Circassia]]n defeat in the [[Caucasian War]]. In 1998 they numbered 200. After the [[Kosovo War]] began, they emigrated to the [[Republic of Adyghea]] in the Russian Federation. There they founded an [[aul]] named [[Mafekhable]] near the republic's capital of [[Maykop]].<ref>http://www.espch.ru/content/view/46/36/</ref>
